In celebration of World Ocean Day 2025, Dickwella Resort & Spa joined hands with the students of Batheegama Maha Vidyalaya and our dedicated hotel team for a meaningful beach cleanup along our beautiful coastline. Together, we took an important step toward preserving our marine environment.

To further engage and inspire the students, an art competition was organized where they creatively expressed their thoughts on ocean conservation. Winners were awarded at our Turtle Conservation Hub, a space launched on World Turtle Day 2025 to raise awareness about protecting endangered sea turtles.

We remain committed to fostering environmental awareness and encouraging the next generation to become passionate advocates for the ocean.

latestPosts.caption:
In celebration of World Environment Day 2025, Dickwella Resort & Spa by @brownshotelsandresorts brought the theme “Beat Plastic Pollution” to life through a series of striking art installations made entirely from discarded plastic. Each piece tells a silent story—of ocean life under threat, of beauty lost, and of hope being rebuilt.

Extending their commitment beyond the resort, the team also carried out a meaningful tree planting initiative at Batheegama Maha Vidyalaya, helping to green the school premises and inspire the next generation to care for the planet.

From creative expression to hands-on action, Dickwella Resort & Spa continues to turn awareness into impact—protecting nature, one thoughtful step at a time.

Caring for nature...is in our nature. 🌿🌍

At Browns Hotels & Resorts, we don’t just exist in nature, we live by its rhythm. From nurturing bees to protecting sea turtles and restoring coastal ecosystems, every step we take is rooted in purpose.

This #EnvironmentDay, join us in celebrating the wild, the rare, and the pure and why they’re all worth protecting.
